  "url": "",
  "description": "The Lookup TOP replaces color values in the TOP image connected to its first input with values derived from a lookup table created from its second input or a lookup table created using the CHOP parameter. When using the 2nd input, the lookup table is created by defining a line (start and end position) on the TOP image. When using a CHOP the lookup table is created directly from the CHOP's values and the 2nd input is ignored.",
  "summary": "The Lookup TOP replaces color values in the TOP image connected to its first input with values derived from a lookup table created from its second input or a lookup table created using the CHOP parame",
